news.news: McBride (hamstring) has been ruled out for Monday's game against the Magic, James L. Edwards III of The Athletic reports.
news.analysis: McBride will miss a fourth straight game due to a left hamstring strain that he suffered during pregame warmups Jan. 1, and his next opportunity to suit up will be Wednesday against the Raptors. Landry Shamet and Cameron Payne will continue to see increased playing time off the bench due to McBride's injury.
